sql:
SELECT o.date_order_placed
FROM Orders o
JOIN (
    SELECT customer_id
    FROM Customer_Payment_Methods
    GROUP BY customer_id
    HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT payment_method_code) >= 2
) cpm ON o.customer_id = cpm.customer_id;
question: List the order date of the orders who are placed by customers with at least 2 payment methods.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT o.date_order_placed
FROM Orders o
JOIN Customer_Payment_Methods cpm ON o.customer_id = cpm.customer_id
GROUP BY o.order_id, o.date_order_placed, o.customer_id
HAVING (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Customer_Payment_Methods WHERE customer_id = o.customer_id) >= 2
